&+R12/09/06&n
  &+GEpic Zone Changes Part II&n
- There is a new command, "epic zones" which shows you all the epic zones in the
  world.
- Epic zones that are done too frequently will become less valuable, and epic zones
  that are rarely done will become even more valuable over time (up to 2x!). The
  epic zone listing will show epic zones that are particularly common or rare.
- This feature does not affect the epic leveling, if you have enough exp and epics 
  for the stone level you will level regardless of the frequency.
- As with any new feature, it is liable to be tweaked for specifics, so don't panic :)

&+R07/09/06&n
- Mortals can now use the "arti unique" and "arti ioun" commands. The list of
  uniques on mobs is still purchasable from the mob in Aravne.

&+R06/09/06&n
  &+GEpic Zone Changes&n
- There is now no epic zone trophy penalty (you can still see your trophy, but it
  doesn't affect the epic payout).
- When touching a stone, everyone in your group in the room will automatically
  receive epics. There is no group size limit, the epics will be shared equally.
- Epic leveling after level 51, like 44-51, now only requires you to level at 
  one of the listed zones (how this works is liable to change in the near future, 
  but for now: &+Renjoy&n!)
- 1.0 frags is now worth 20 epic points.

&+R29/08/06&n
- New command, "trophy frags", will show you the people you've fragged, and how
  many times you've been in on the kill (not the total value of frags gained from
  them). This is just for your own private viewing pleasure, having a high number 
  here won't affect frags gained in the future.
- Stat pools no longer have the chance to reduce your stats.
- Guild golems no longer require upkeep.

