&+R7/06/06&n
- &+LDayblind for Evils&n
  Relive the glory days of Duris by being blind during the day (as an evil) or hiding
  like a wussy until the sun comes up (as a good)!

  The main evil races (Drow, Duergar, Troll, Ogre, Githyanki) can no longer see during the
  day. Orcs and neutral races (Minotaurs, Harpies) are unaffected.

  Races affected by this can hide in forest or swamp squares and are unaffected (although
  they can't see the map during the day).

  Due to the special Ship Sunglasses installed in all ships in the world of Duris, all races
  can see the same while sailing.

  Globe of darkness is now a self-only spell, available to necromancers at the 9th circle.

  Nightbringer lost globe of darkness, but has a new proc.

  All of this is subject to tweaking, so please test it out, and we will be monitoring the
  situation if anything needs to be changed.

  Since this is a major change, I (Torgal) will be doing race changes for evils over level 30
  affected by this if desired (up to and including racewar change if you want) for &+Wone week only&n 
  (until Wed, 14/6/06). Please don't bug the other gods if they don't want to bother 
  with this.

&+R6/06/06&n
- &+GEpic Zone Trophy&n
  Right now, there are 81 epic zones on Duris. Since the beginning of the wipe, only
  48 of them have been done, and many of them multiple times.

  Due to this, the Gods of Duris have implemented an epic zone trophy system. If you
  keep doing the same zone over and over, the non-pvp epics you receive will decrease.
  You can "roll" the trophy like mob trophy, but it would be even better to take
  this opportunity to discover the zones out there that you've never done before!

  The command "epic trophy" will show you the epic zones you have accomplished.

- The "epic" command will show you the top players on both sides by epics.
- Tracks left behind by players will now no longer give the race name.
- Enhance spells available to psionicists are now bonus type spells instead
  of basically setting stats to 100.

