  It isn't anymore.

&+R4/06/06&n
- The spells magic missile, chill touch, burning hands, acid blast, shocking grasp, 
  lightning bolt, cone of cold, ice storm, fireball, bigby's clenched fist, and bigby's
  crushing hand have been recalibrated to be more or less a linear progression in damage 
  instead of the total willy-nilly they've been for the past 10 years. Fist and hand do
  approximately the same damage as they did before, but their failed spell save damages
  aren't quite so ridiculous.
  These are all still subject to being balanced, so please don't panic.
- Stone skin, shadow shield and biofeedback are now not stackable with each other.
- Air magi are now perm haste, and their hastes and air form spells also last a bit longer.

