The races of &+rDuris&N have evolved...
&N&+bOgres&N, &+LMino&N&+rtaurs&N, &+gCen&+Ltaurs&N, and &+gTrolls &Nare the only large races. &+BBarbarians &Nhave
been reduced in size to medium and gained more moves. A shield is grand thing to
have as they grant much more armor class.  &+rRogues&N are again the only class to be
able to trip; meanwhile, &+WRe&+Lave&+Wrs&N have learned to springleap, &+GRangers&N have forgot
how it was they once bashed, and the time a victim must stay on the ground after
being lept at has been reduced.  Likewise, &+RMauling&N and &+LGazing&N now take less of a
toll on others. &+BWarriors&N who attempt to bash without a shield worn also may note
their victim standing a bit sooner. &N&+cHitters&N have had their hitpoints downgraded.
&+YMountain Dwarves &Nand &+rDuergar Dwarves&N have survived long against magic. Thus, the
Dwarves have developed a damage reduction innate towards the most general magic.
The &+RGnomish&N Schools of Engineering and Magic have finished their work on another
advancement for their race: &+bultravision&N. The condition of your armor affects the
amount your armor protects you, keep it in excellent &+Crepair&N. &+gDruids&N are now more
closely guarded with their spells; no longer will others benefit by serendipity,
also regeneration is now self only. Summoning cyclones now takes longer. Shields
are no longer usable by the fledgling &+gDruids&N. Rumors state, upon specialization,
the skill returns.  The &+YConjurer's Conjecture&N daily has reported that a new copy
of the Conjurer Spellbook has come out.  The effects minorly paralysis will fade
faster as will the unconsciousness resulting from headbutt. The time of &+Rhard&N&+rcore&N
is no more. The time when &+gDruids&N and &+WRe&+Lave&+Wrs&N strayed from their prime classes is
no more, they may no longer multiclass.  &+WPaladins &Nand &+LAnti-Paladins&N were granted
new innate auras to aid their groups in exchange for their spells of protection.
&+LAnti-paladins&N can now 'descend' into the depths of evil and become dreadlords.
(&+mNecromancers &Ndecided it was too dangerous&N).  &+yGuardians &Ncan now guard and defend.


&+mNecromancer &Nspecs have been swapped around:
&+mDiabolis&N necros have studied how to create powerful golems, the art of
unmaking corpses to heal themselves, and how to search the ground in
order to exhume corpses. They are also masters of the power of undead,
to the point where they can cast the destroy undead spell.

&+mNe&+Lcrol&N&+myte&N necros are the masters of groups of undead; their pets never
turn on them, and they can see corpses on the overland map. They also
have proficiency in staffs of all sorts (but they are no longer
masters), and are able to control slightly more undead. They also
automatically mummify a corpse if they happen to strike the killing blow.

&+LReaper&N necros seek after the living in order to bring them to the realm
of the dead. They are excellent hand-to-hand fighters with stabbing or
slashing blades, and they are able to summon a doom blade to slash their
foes. They can summon the shadows to attack with the power of the mind,
and have learned how to return to life while in a vampiric trance via
their new "remort" command.

&+WThe Economy of &+rDuris&N &+Wis changing...&N
The Shopkeepers of Duris have joined in a pact: to adjust the prices in relation
to how common the item is.  They have introduced a new line of products as well,
&+Wbandages&N which can be found in any local store or learned about in help bandage.
&+cFirst Aid&N is now the life saving command and can be used more often.  The way in
which prices were done for quests has changed. &+yBartenders&N the world over will be
glad to give them out. How often they are done affects the experience earned and
money given. The &+GWit&N&+gch Doc&+Gtor&N has grown too frail to wander about the mountains.
The new economy has allowed Ramous to make additions to his town; &+CVerspin&N is now
much more interactive, also.  A "pitty" area has been added to the town as well.
The Council of Shipwrights have spent much time in deliberation, they decided to
create some price adjustments on the four types of ships they now make.  The vast 
&+gswamps&N of the continent of evil have become infested with all sorts of nasty
creatures.  Furthermore, the &+LDark&N&+yPeak&N mountains have become overrun with greedy
orcs that populate the cities located therein.  The hometown of the &+GGoblins&N has shifted
to a new location, and three new &+GGoblin&N areas have been discovered.  The great and
versatile &+yFerry System&N has also seen great improvements, including new ferries and
an all around faster ride.  The village of &+RTentro&N has been found, and also the
high elf city of &+YShaledrieth&N, guardians of a mystical &+Ysunwell&N.  Time to explore!
&+yMercenaries&N are now the true bounty hunters, the only class able to earn money as
a bonus to completing bartender quests.  More on &+yFerries&N, they now appear as an &+WF&N
on the map.  The SeaStalker's ferry route has been changed, going from the Piers of Fehlnan
to the Jade Empire to Fort Boyard and back, for only the price of a ticket!
When someone bids on an auction, the ending time is now postponed 5 minutes.

Regarding experience and levels...
Experience has become harder for all.  The effects of trophy on experience shall
be noticed by all; yet, moreso by &+rEvils&N. &+rEvils&N also will notice that exp doesn't
go as fast if their group size is any bigger than three. Additionally, &+rEvils&N can
not regain as much experience after being &+Wresurrected&N. The experience derived by
Player vs Player, if within range, is more substantial.  &+WAdvancing past level 45
&+Wrequires epics, see help epic for exact numbers. &N Also, only twice per level can
you complete a bartender quest; only two per real-life day may be completed once
you attain level 50 and above.

A few not so minor, miscellaneous changes...
The artifacts of &+rDuris&N have been located by a wise &+Ycreature&N somewhere in &+gAvarne&N.
The &+Celite&N&+y guards of &+GWoodseer &Nhave grown tired of the constant abuse, expect more
security by the Halflings. &+WRolling you character has no randomness to it. Ingame
&+Wyou may improve your stats for a bit of cash.&N The magical, amazing power of some
swords has been lost: &+GPathfinder&N and the &+rflaming&+L gre&Nats&+Lword &Nno longer respond to
commands. Due to the Guild Golem union, Golems are no longer required to work as
hard when they deny you access. They lightly shove you down now which will allow
you to stand immediately. The &+ymaps&N of &+rDuris &Nhave changed: &+ybeaches&N now abound for
your docking pleasure. &+RThe inhabitants of &n&+rDuris&+R have forgotten how to form ranks
&+Rin combat.

The Nuts and Bolts...
Upon login, the game now automatically picks &+RA&+BN&+GS&+YI&N terminal. &+rDuris is up on a new
machine and should work much better: steps have been taken the step to &+Rdual core&N
and &+Y64bit platforms&N.  Also, multiple &+Ldisc drives will now make pfile backup much
more secure! The mud has not moved.

